abstract: Some Republican and Democratic members of the House of Representatives have common ground: their exercise routine.
snippet: Some Republican and Democratic members of the House of Representatives have common ground: their exercise routine.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A new muscle-crushing, sweat-inducing workout has infiltrated the inner sanctum of Congress, the members-only gym of the House of Representatives. And it is called, simply, the “Markwayne Mullin.”

abstract: Representative Eric Cantor, the House majority leader, lost his primary race, setting off a political frenzy. Militants in Iraq have also retaken areas of the country that Americans once held. Both events will dominate the conversation on the Sunday shows.
snippet: Representative Eric Cantor, the House majority leader, lost his primary race, setting off a political frenzy. Militants in Iraq have also retaken areas of the country that Americans once held. Both events will dominate the conversation on the Sund...
lead_paragraph: A primary race in Virginia rocked the political world when Representative Eric Cantor, the House majority leader, lost to his Tea Party-backed opponent David Brat, an economics professor. By the following day, Mr. Cantor announced that he would resign his leadership position by July 31. Mr. Cantor will appear on both ABC’s “This Week and CNN’s “State of the Union,” to give his opinion on why he lost his congressional seat and what went wrong with his campaign.

abstract: The tragic shootings at Fort Hood will dominate the conversation on the Sunday shows — particularly the treatment of mental health problems in the military.
snippet: The tragic shootings at Fort Hood will dominate the conversation on the Sunday shows — particularly the treatment of mental health problems in the military.
lead_paragraph: Fort Hood, Tex., suffered a devastating blow this week when Specialist Ivan Antonio Lopez opened fire at the Army base, killing three and wounding 16 of his fellow soldiers, then taking his own life. Five years ago, another soldier went on a similar shooting rampage at Fort Hood, killing 13 people. On Thursday, Defense Secretary Chuck Hagel struggled to explain why new security measures had not been effective.

abstract: A White House report recommending curtailing the powers of the National Security Agency and imposing more oversight is the main top on Sunday’s talk shows.
snippet: A White House report recommending curtailing the powers of the National Security Agency and imposing more oversight is the main top on Sunday’s talk shows.
lead_paragraph: This week, a White House-appointed panel recommended that President Obama rein in the National Security Agency and impose more oversight. Also, a United States District Court judge ruled Monday that an N.S.A. program that systematically collects records of American phone calls is probably unconstitutional, but he stayed his order while the case is appealed.

abstract: After an end-of-the-year news conference, President Obama and his family touched down in Hawaii, his boyhood home, for a holiday vacation.
snippet: After an end-of-the-year news conference, President Obama and his family touched down in Hawaii, his boyhood home, for a holiday vacation.
lead_paragraph: HONOLULU — After an end-of-the-year news conference whose first question — “Has this been the worst year of your presidency?” — offered a trenchant reminder of President Obama’s troubled 2013, the president seemed especially ready for a break from the nation’s capital.
headline_main: Obamas Arrive in Hawaii for Vacation

abstract: Democrats in Washington, in Texas and around the nation, marshaled by female activists, are clamoring for Wendy Davis to run for governor in 2014 -- no matter that her chances of winning are slim.
snippet: Democrats in Washington, in Texas and around the nation, marshaled by female activists, are clamoring for Wendy Davis to run for governor in 2014 -- no matter that her chances of winning are slim.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Not since Sarah Palin’s splashy debut in U.S. politics in August 2008 has any female politician come out of obscurity and, virtually overnight, captured the eye of the political and media world like the belle from Fort Worth, Texas: Wendy Davis, the state senator whose marathon filibuster of a restrictive abortion bill is now history.
headline_main: Democrats Put Hope in Texas Star
headline_print_headline: Democrats Put Hope in Texas Star

abstract: Key lawmakers working on the Senate proposal to overhaul immigration and the director of the National Security Agency will join the Sunday shows.
snippet: Key lawmakers working on the Senate proposal to overhaul immigration and the director of the National Security Agency will join the Sunday shows.
lead_paragraph: There was good news last week for the Senate proposal to overhaul immigration, as two Republicans struck a deal on border security with the group of eight senators working on the bill. Now it looks likely that the proposal will see a vote before the Fourth of July recess.

abstract: Senator Kirsten E. Gillibrand is leading a bipartisan group of women in a fierce battle to change attitudes about sexual crimes in the military and the legal system used to address them.
snippet: Senator Kirsten E. Gillibrand is leading a bipartisan group of women in a fierce battle to change attitudes about sexual crimes in the military and the legal system used to address them.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Shocking the gridlocked Congress into action, a half dozen or so bipartisan female senators are escalating their war on sexual crimes in the military and deploying their outrage, clout and legions of supporters against a rigid military structure and its male-dominated ranks.

headline_main: Women in Congress Confront the Military on Sexual Assault

abstract: Lawmakers at the center of the investigation into the September attacks in Benghazi, Libya, join the Sunday shows to look back at a week of intensified scrutiny and talk about what comes next.
snippet: Lawmakers at the center of the investigation into the September attacks in Benghazi, Libya, join the Sunday shows to look back at a week of intensified scrutiny and talk about what comes next.
lead_paragraph: As scrutiny of the September attacks on the American diplomatic compound in Benghazi, Libya, intensifies, Representative Darrell Issa of California, chairman of the House oversight committee, and Senator Dianne Feinstein of California, chairwoman of the Intelligence Committee, will join NBC’s “Meet the Press” on Sunday.

abstract: The Sunday shows talk about the budget battles on Capitol Hill, national security and the new head of the Catholic Church.
snippet: The Sunday shows talk about the budget battles on Capitol Hill, national security and the new head of the Catholic Church.
lead_paragraph: In the wake of President Obama’s meetings on Capitol Hill with lawmakers from both parties, the Sunday shows feature discussions of whether Congress is any closer to a fiscal agreement.
